   TOP
</P>
<P>
   Lead:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-DIPLO (Washington) _ Response to the release of the
America soldiers, and other developments, including an expected
meeting between President Clinton and the Russian special envoy for
the Balkans, Viktor Chernomyrdin. By Jane Perlez.
</P>
<P>
   Single column lede.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Center:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-SOLDIERS (Ramstein Air Base, Germany) _ After 31 days of
virtual isolation in a Yugoslav prisons, where one man said he
found comfort in an American flag he drew on toilet paper and the
other two found comfort in prayer, three freed U.S. soldiers were
cheered on their arrival here Sunday and pronounced in apparent
good health. By Susan Sachs.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Off-lead (national edition):
</P>
<P>
   CHARITY-ADS-CRACKDOWN (Undated) _ Nonprofit organizations take
in roughly half a billion dollars a year for lending their good
names to the marketing of everything from nicotine patches to pain
relievers. The proliferation of such pitches, and the fact that
consumers may mistakenly believe they are endorsements, has come to
the attention of state regulators, and now 16 state attorneys
general want to stem the tide of ads. By Reed Abelson.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``f'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   (In New York edition)
</P>
<P>
   PBA-ELECTION (New York) _ As Patrolmen's Benevolent Association
prepares to elect a president this month, the campaign is revealing
deep divisions within its leadership, even as many officers look to
the organization for help in reviving the force's flagging morale.
By Kevin Flynn.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   ABOVE FOLD:
</P>
<P>
   KOSOVO-MASSACRE (Kukes, Albania) _ It lasted no more than three
minutes, three minutes of savagery unleashed without even a word.
``They just started shooting and I got hit in the shoulder. The
dead bodies behind me pushed me over the cliff and into the stream.
I was lucky because all of the dead bodies fell on top of me.''
Isuf Zheniqi, who said he survived when 58 men died in a massacre
in southwestern Kosovo more than a month ago, speaks out
hesitantly, fearing Serbian forces might take revenge on members of
his family still in Kosovo. By Anthony DePalma.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   BELOW FOLD:
</P>
<P>
   COLO-SCHOOL-INTERNET (Undated) _ Reports that the two students
involved in the shootings in Littleton, Colo., had played violent
computer games and that one of them had posted descriptions of
making pipe bombs on a Web site appear to have sharpened parents'
concerns over the online activities that are often the most
mysterious corners of their children's lives. For many, it was the
one checked item on a mental list of comparisons to those
responsible for the Colorado massacre. By Amy Harmon.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:30 p.m. ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Reefer to:
</P>
<P>
   NEW-FOUNDATION (Undated) _ A new nonprofit foundation is formed
to finance innovative art shunned by the NEA. By Judith H.
Dobrzynski.
</P>
<P>
   With photo.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 6:30 p.m. ET in ``e'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   &UR; BOTTOM:  &LR;
</P>
<P>
   INDIA-WOMEN-POLITICS (Chijarasi, India) _ Almost a million women
have been elected to village governing panels since India adopted a
constitutional amendment in 1993. Still expected to veil their
faces and submit to male elders, more and more women are now
challenging centuries-old, feudal hierarchies. By Celia Dugger.
</P>
<P>
   With photos.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 8:15 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   Reefer to:
</P>
<P>
   LONDON-BOMBING (London) _ British police charged a 22-year-old
engineer with murder Sunday after three crude and brutal nail-bomb
attacks on ethnic minorities and gays that killed three people,
wounded more than 100 and confronted Britons with a bloody
challenge to their avowed tolerance. By Alan Cowell.
</P>
<P>
   (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``i'' news file.)
</P>
