   BURN-BOY (Los Angeles) _ Despite horrible, disfiguring burns,
10-year-old Denis Nefedova isn't shy about going out and enjoying
the sights and hoopla that make Los Angeles so wonderfully
different than his tiny island home in Russia. By Steve Carney.
(Will move in the ``n'' California and ``a'' national news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DENVER-GRIEF (Littleton, Colo.) _ This area's grief in the wake
of the Columbine High School shootings is as broad as a country
mourning a national hero, but as personal as a family struggling
with its most intimate pain. By Greg Gittrich and Beth Barrett.
Editors note: The reporters spent the last week in Colorado
covering the aftermath of the school massacre as part of a team of
reporters working for the Daily News' sister newspaper, The Denver
