<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following for
clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of Monday, May 3,
and thereafter. If you have any questions, please call Veronica
Villarreal at (206) 448-8342.
</P>
<P>
   SALMON-RECOVERY (MONROE, Wash.) _ The rebirth of the Haskell
Slough, a few hundred yards from the fury of the swollen Skykomish
River, is the work of a coalition of community and tribal groups,
landowners and volunteers. By any measure, it seems an undisputed
success. But it is, in fact, at the heart of an intense dispute
over Washington state's salmon recovery strategy. At issue is who
will control the tens of millions of dollars in salmon money and
where it will be spent.
</P>
<P>
   By Robert Gavin. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   SCHOOL-VIOLENCE (Seattle) _ The sheer magnitude of the slaughter
at Littleton's Columbine High School has put Puget Sound-area
schools on high alert and prompted sober reviews of school
security, including a special meeting this week between Seattle
police and school officials.
</P>
<P>
   By Ruth Teichroeb. (Story will move in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   QUILT-MILLENNIUM (Seattle) _ Millennium madness is not confined
to survivalists stockpiling goods or frenzied computer experts
swatting software bugs. Quilters are already celebrating the
thousand-year change. Stitch by stitch they're creating their own
historic millennium quilts _ quilts with 2,000 tiny pieces.
</P>
<P>
   By Susan Phinney. (Story will move in the ``l'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-SONICS (Seattle) _ Struggling to make the playoffs, the
Seatte SuperSonics lose to the Los Angeles Lakers, 91-84.
</P>
<P>
   By Ronald Tillery. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BBA-MARINERS (Seattle) _ The Seattle Mariners play host to the
Toronto Blue Jays.
</P>
<P>
   By Tyler Kepner. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BKN-THIEL-SONICS (Seattle) _ A column on the SuperSonics-Lakers
game.
</P>
<P>
   By Art Thiel. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
</P>
