<HEADLINE>
THIS WEEK'S TV HIGHLIGHTS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By TOM HOFFARTH  
 c.1999 Los Angeles Daily News  
TODAY 
How many Cuban National Team baseball players does it take to cause
an international incident? As many as the Orioles can stash in
their dugout to help get them out of the AL East basement.
Baltimore Orioles vs. Cuban National Team, Fox Sports Net West 2,
10 p.m. (delayed). 
TUESDAY 
Felipe Alou, who snubbed the Dodgers in the offseason, manages an
Expos team flopping around with a 7-16 record, 9{ games back in the
NL East. And no one in Montreal cares. What a sweet gig. Dodgers at
Montreal, Fox Sports West 2, 4 p.m. 
WEDNESDAY 
The punch-drunk NBA regular season comes to a staggering finish
with the Lakers guaranteed a playoff spot and the Clippers out of
it. We needed a 50-game schedule to figure that out? Miami at New
York, TBS, 5 p.m.; Seattle at Clippers, Channel 9, 7:30 p.m.;
Portland at Lakers, Fox Sports West, 7:30 p.m. (Note: The NBA
playoffs begin Saturday. NBC has a game at 2:30 p.m. and TNT has
one at 6 p.m. Sunday, NBC has games at 9:30 a.m., noon and 2:30
p.m.)  
THURSDAY 
It's Gabe Kapler's opportunity to get some TV time for the family
back home in Woodland Hills, but the guy the Angels really want to
see is Tigers reliever Mel Rojas. The exiled Dodger gave up 11
earned runs (five in the fifth, six in the sixth) during a
12/3-inning stint against Seattle the other day _ and managed to
avoid taking the loss. That went to C.J. Nitkowski, who threw five
pitches and issued a walk _ which came around to put the Mariners
ahead, thanks to Big Mel. Angels at Detroit, Fox Sports West, 4
p.m. 
FRIDAY 
Overexposed Fox Sports News anchor/celebrity Keith Olbermann, fresh
off a second-place finish on ``Jeopardy!,'' completes a week's run
on ``Hollywood Squares'' surrounded by cast members from
``Everybody Loves Raymond.'' We know that former ``Squares'' host
Peter Marshall's son, Pete LaCock, used to play for the Chicago
Cubs. But that's where the sports connection must end. ``Hollywood
Squares,'' Channel 2, 7:30 p.m. 
SATURDAY 
Why isn't Pauley Pavilion the permanent home for the NCAA
volleyball finals? 'Cause UCLA might get an extra home game each
year? Not this time. In Thursday's semifinals, Long Beach State
will face Indiana-Purdue of Ft. Wayne and Brigham Young will take
on Penn State. NCAA men's volleyball finals, ESPN2, 8 p.m.
(delayed). (Also: ESPN2 has one semifinal live Thursday at 8:30
p.m. and the other on tape Friday at 9:30 p.m.) 
SUNDAY 
If she wants to watch the Dodgers or Lakers on her special day,
then it's her choice. Mother knows best. Here's an idea: Suggest a
brunch down at the local sports bar. Dodgers vs. Florida, Fox
Sports West 2, 1:10 p.m. 

